FBIS3-13453 "drnes050_o_94006" FBIS-NES-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 SYRIA Hebron Massacre Continues To Threaten Peace JN1103082994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0545 GMT 11 Mar 94 JN1103082994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [From the press review] [Text] Discussing the UN Security Council's deliberations on the Hebron massacre, AL-BA'TH writes in its "With the Events" column: Awaiting a UN Security Council resolution and following world demand for an Israeli withdrawal and the implementation of the Geneva Conventions on the protection of civilians in time of war, the threats to peace, posed by the Ibrahimi Mosque massacre, have not gone away. Nor will the massacre lose its influence on the credibility of the UN Security Council, which is still holding consultations as if the massacre were less significant than Lockerbie or less vicious than the reasons that prompted UN troops to land in more than one capital of the post-Cold War world.
